      "solution": "def reines(n, p) :\n    # Initialisation\n    if n == 1 :\n        liste = [[str(i+1)] for i in range(p)]\n        return liste\n    # Hérédité\n    else :\n        liste_prec = reines(n-1, p)\n        liste_new = []\n        for solution_prec in liste_prec :\n            for i in range(p) :\n                p = i + 1\n                valable = True\n                # Colonne occupée ?\n                if str(p) in solution_prec :\n                    valable = False\n                else :\n                    # Diagonales occupées ?\n                    for j in range(1, n) :\n                        k = int(solution_prec[j-1])\n                        if n - j == abs(p - k) :\n                            valable = False\n                # Validation\n                if valable :\n                    liste_new.append(solution_prec + [str(p)])\n        return liste_new\n\nn = int(input())\nprint(len(reines(n, n)))",
      "statement": "We have to place [[n]] queens on a chessboard  made of [[n]] x [[n]] squares.\nWe need to place all of them in such a way that none of them is in direct contact nor attacking another one.\n(meaning only one queen is occupying each line, column and diagonal)\n\nExample with [[n]] = {{4}}, [[s]] = {{2}} solutions :\n\n`- Q - -\n- - - Q\nQ - - -\n- - Q -`\nand\n\n`- - Q -\nQ - - -\n- - - Q\n- Q - -`",
